  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>There are some users that must exist on the wiki, but no one should be able to
make an OpenHatch website account by the name -- otherwise they'd be able to
impersonate those accounts on the wiki. They are:

* Admin
* Sufjan
* Spam cleanup script

So we should write something in the Django user creation code that prevents
people from signing up with those usernames.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
